quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,97,"And say: "
  23,98,""
  23,99,"Until, when death comes to one of them (those who join partners with Allâh), he says: "
  25,43,"Have you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) seen him who has taken as his ilâh (god) his own vain desire? Would you then be a Wakîl (a disposer of his affairs or a watcher) over him?"
  25,44,"Or do you think that most of them hear or understand? They are only like cattle - nay, they are even farther astray from the Path (i.e. even worse than cattle)."
  25,45,"Have you not seen how your Lord spread the shadow. If He willed, He could have made it still - But We have made the sun its guide (i.e. after the sunrise, the shadow shrinks and vanishes at midnoon and then again appears in the afternoon with the decline of the sun, and had there been no sunlight, there would have been no shadow)."
  26,16,""
  26,17,""
  26,18,"[Fir‘aun (Pharaoh)] said [to Mûsâ (Moses)]: "